{
  "_comment": "REL-5 multi-window multi-burn-rate alert policies — fast-burn (page) + slow-burn (ticket) per SLO. Uses the SLO-native select_slo_burn_rate filter, which is baseline-agnostic (operates on budget consumed, not raw error rate) so it works even for the 90% latency SLO where a raw-rate threshold would exceed 100% (see slis-slos-error-budget.md §4). BEFORE APPLY: (1) substitute ${PROJECT_ID}, ${SLO_*} resource names (projects/$PROJECT_ID/services/<svc>/serviceLevelObjectives/<sloId>), and ${NOTIFICATION_CHANNEL_ID} (projects/$PROJECT_ID/notificationChannels/XXXX). (2) Apply each policy separately: `gcloud alpha monitoring policies create --policy-from-file <one-policy.json> --project $PROJECT_ID`. Fast-burn: lookbackPeriod 3600s (1h) + burn rate >14.4. Slow-burn: lookbackPeriod 21600s (6h) + burn rate >6. (The short-window 'still-burning' guard is added as a second condition in the page policies; combined via combiner AND.) Route ALL alerts to ONE low-cost channel (email) at beta — add a paid PagerDuty channel id to the fast-burn policies' notificationChannels only when a B2G SLA requires 24/7 on-call.",
  "policies": [
    {
      "displayName": "[PAGE] Arbor availability fast-burn (14.4x, 1h+5m)",
      "combiner": "AND",
      "conditions": [
        {
          "displayName": "availability budget burning >14.4x over 1h",
          "conditionThreshold": {
            "filter": "select_slo_burn_rate(\"${SLO_AVAILABILITY}\", \"3600s\")",
            "comparison": "COMPARISON_GT",
            "thresholdValue": 14.4,
            "duration": "0s",
            "trigger": { "count": 1 }
          }
        },
        {
          "displayName": "availability budget still burning >14.4x over 5m",
          "conditionThreshold": {
            "filter": "select_slo_burn_rate(\"${SLO_AVAILABILITY}\", \"300s\")",
            "comparison": "COMPARISON_GT",
            "thresholdValue": 14.4,
            "duration": "0s",
            "trigger": { "count": 1 }
          }
        }
      ],
      "notificationChannels": ["${NOTIFICATION_CHANNEL_ID}"],
      "severity": "CRITICAL",
      "documentation": { "content": "Availability error budget (SLO 99.5%) is burning >14.4x. ~2% of the 30-day budget will be gone within ~1h. See docs/ops/slo.md §4 + dr-runbook.md (REL-1). Likely causes: 5xx spike, Cloud Run instance unavailability (check REL-4 readiness), regional event.", "mimeType": "text/markdown" }
